            ['title' => 'Introduction to the Quran: The Book of Allah', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 20, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn what the Quran is, how it was revealed, how it was preserved, and why it is the most important book for every Muslim\'s life.', 'instructions' => '1. Explain: the Quran is the direct word of Allah revealed to the Prophet Muhammad ﷺ over 23 years.\n2. Discuss: how was it preserved? (oral transmission + written compilation under Abu Bakr and Uthman)\n3. Key facts: 114 surahs, 30 juz, 6,236 ayat.\n4. Why do we recite it correctly? Introduce the concept of tajweed.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran copy, pencil, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Describe the revelation, preservation, and structure of the Quran', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Al-Fatiha: The Opening', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 9, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Memorise and understand Surah Al-Fatiha — the most recited surah in the Quran, repeated at least 17 times daily in prayer — exploring its meaning, structure, and importance.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite Al-Fatiha from memory.\n2. Translate each ayah line by line.\n3. Discuss the 3 parts: praise of Allah, description of Allah, dua.\n4. Why is it called "Umm al-Quran" (Mother of the Quran)?\n5. Recite again with meaning in mind.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation reference', 'learning_objectives' => 'Recite Al-Fatiha from memory and explain the meaning of each ayah', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Tajweed Basics: The Rules of Recitation', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 10, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn 5 essential tajweed rules — madd (lengthening), sukoon, tanween, the rules of noon sakinah — and apply them to recitation of Al-Fatiha.', 'instructions' => '1. Explain why tajweed matters: correct pronunciation preserves the meaning of Allah\'s word.\n2. Teach 5 rules with examples.\n3. Apply each rule to 2 verses from Al-Fatiha.\n4. Record recitation, listen back, identify where to improve.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, tajweed chart, recording device', 'learning_objectives' => 'Apply 5 tajweed rules correctly when reciting Al-Fatiha', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Ayat al-Kursi: The Verse of the Throne', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Memorise and deeply understand Ayat al-Kursi (2:255) — the greatest verse in the Quran — exploring its description of Allah\'s attributes and the protection it offers.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite Ayat al-Kursi.\n2. Translate and analyse: list every attribute of Allah mentioned in this single verse.\n3. Memorise in stages: break into 5 sections, master each before joining.\n4. When is it especially recommended to recite it? (After each prayer, before sleeping)', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation reference', 'learning_objectives' => 'Recite Ayat al-Kursi from memory and identify all Allah\'s attributes within it', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'The Last 3 Surahs: Ikhlas, Falaq, Naas', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 9, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Memorise and understand the last 3 surahs of the Quran — Ikhlas (pure tawheed), Falaq (protection from external harm), and Naas (protection from internal whispers).', 'instructions' => '1. Recite all three from memory.\n2. Translate each and discuss: what harms are we seeking protection from?\n3. Surah Ikhlas: "Say He is Allah, the One." Explain Ahad and Samad.\n4. Practice: recite all three in sequence as morning/evening protection.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation reference', 'learning_objectives' => 'Recite Surahs Ikhlas, Falaq, and Naas from memory with understanding of meaning', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Understanding Surah Al-Asr', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Memorise and deeply study Surah Al-Asr — one of the most comprehensive surahs in the Quran — exploring the 4 conditions for success according to the scholars.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite Surah Al-Asr.\n2. Imam Al-Shafi\'i said: "If nothing was revealed except this surah, it would be enough for humanity." Why?\n3. Identify the 4 conditions for success: Iman, righteous deeds, mutual encouragement of truth, mutual encouragement of patience.\n4. Write how you apply each condition in your life.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Recite Surah Al-Asr from memory and explain its 4 conditions for success', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Kahf: Every Friday', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn about Surah Al-Kahf — its Friday recommendation, its 4 main stories, and the protection of the first and last 10 verses from the Dajjal.', 'instructions' => '1. Discuss: why is Al-Kahf recommended on Fridays? (light from one Friday to the next)\n2. Map the 4 stories: People of the Cave, The Two Men, Musa and Khidr, Dhul-Qarnayn.\n3. What is the main theme connecting all 4 stories? (Tests: religion, wealth, knowledge, power)\n4. Memorise the first 5 verses of Al-Kahf.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation reference, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify Al-Kahf\'s 4 stories and their shared theme, and memorise the first 5 verses', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Juz \'Amma: Overview and Memorisation Plan', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 10, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => true, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Overview all 37 surahs of Juz \'Amma (30th Juz), create a personal memorisation plan, and track progress over time toward completing a full Juz.', 'instructions' => '1. List all 37 surahs of Juz \'Amma with their page count.\n2. Mark which you have already memorised.\n3. Create a schedule: 1 new surah per week (adjust based on length).\n4. Set up a progress tracker on coloured circles — fill in each circle as a surah is memorised.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, coloured markers, progress tracker template', 'learning_objectives' => 'Create a personalised Juz \'Amma memorisation schedule and begin tracking progress', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Names and Attributes of Allah (Asma al-Husna)', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn 10 names and attributes of Allah from Asma al-Husna, their meanings, and connect each to a Quranic verse — building a profound knowledge of Who Allah is.', 'instructions' => '1. Introduce the concept: 99 names, "whoever memorises them will enter Jannah."\n2. Study 10 names: Ar-Rahman, Ar-Rahim, Al-Malik, Al-Quddus, As-Salam, Al-Mu\'min, Al-Aziz, Al-Jabbar, Al-Wahhab, Al-Razzaq.\n3. For each: meaning, one Quranic verse, one example of how it appears in daily life.\n4. Begin memorising all 10 this week.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, names of Allah reference card', 'learning_objectives' => 'Explain the meaning of 10 divine names and connect each to a Quranic verse', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'How to Approach the Quran with Tadabbur (Reflection)', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 8, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the concept of tadabbur (deep reflection on Quranic meaning) and apply it to one short surah — reading slowly, pausing, questioning, and journaling reflections.', 'instructions' => '1. Explain tadabbur: not just reciting but pondering deeply.\n2. Read Surah Al-Insan or Surah Al-Ghashiya slowly, one verse at a time.\n3. After each verse: write one question it raises and one feeling it evokes.\n4. At the end: write 3 things you learned about Allah or yourself from this surah.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Apply tadabbur (reflective reading) to a short surah and journal insights', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'The Story of Adam (AS) in the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study the Quranic account of Adam (AS) — creation, the angels\' prostration, Iblis\'s refusal, the garden, the test, the descent, and Allah\'s mercy.', 'instructions' => '1. Read verses on Adam from Surah Al-Baqarah and Al-A\'raf.\n2. Timeline the story: creation, giving of knowledge, command to prostrate, Iblis, descent, repentance, mercy.\n3. Lessons: the danger of arrogance (Iblis), human responsibility, the mercy of Allah.\n4. Write 3 lessons from Adam\'s story for your own life.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, pencil, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Narrate the Quranic story of Adam (AS) and extract 3 personal lessons', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Making a Connection with the Quran Daily', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 20, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Build a daily Quran habit: set a realistic recitation target, create a calm environment, understand what to say before and after recitation.', 'instructions' => '1. Discuss: what is a realistic daily Quran goal for you? (1 page? 3 pages? 5 minutes?)\n2. Set the right environment: wudu, facing qiblah if possible, calm and focused.\n3. Learn what to say before: A\'udhu billah + Bismillah.\n4. Set up a personal Quran diary: date, pages read, one sentence you reflected on.\n5. Commit for 7 days and share how it felt.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Establish a realistic daily Quran habit and begin a Quran reflection diary', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Yasin: The Heart of the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 35, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Introduction to Surah Yasin — its themes of resurrection, the story of the people of the city, the fate of the deniers, and vivid descriptions of Jannah and Jahannam.', 'instructions' => '1. Read a summary of Surah Yasin (36).\n2. Identify 3 main themes: messengers and their rejection, proof of resurrection from nature, description of Jannah and Jahannam.\n3. Memorise the opening 5 verses (Ya-Sin...).\n4. Discuss: why is Yasin called the heart of the Quran?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify the main themes of Surah Yasin and memorise its opening 5 verses', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Understanding Makki and Madani Surahs', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the difference between Makki (revealed in Makkah) and Madani (revealed in Madinah) surahs — their themes, style, and the different needs of the Muslim community at each stage.', 'instructions' => '1. Explain the historical context: 13 years in Makkah (minority, persecution), 10 years in Madinah (community, state).\n2. Makki themes: tawheed, afterlife, prophets\' stories, patience.\n3. Madani themes: laws, fiqh, social rules, hypocrites.\n4. Classify 10 surahs as Makki or Madani and explain the clues.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, reference list, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Distinguish Makki from Madani surahs and explain the different themes in each', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran Recitation Assessment and Progress', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Assess current Quran recitation level — tajweed accuracy, fluency, memorisation — and set a personalised 30-day improvement target with a daily schedule.', 'instructions' => '1. Self-assessment: recite 5 recently learned verses. Parent or teacher marks: correct, needs work, incorrect.\n2. Identify top 3 areas to improve: specific letters, madd rules, fluency.\n3. Set a 30-day target: how many pages to memorise, which rule to perfect.\n4. Design a daily schedule: time, surah, target.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, assessment checklist, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Complete a Quran recitation assessment and produce a 30-day personal improvement plan', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Mulk: Seeking Protection Every Night', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Mulk (67) — its nightly recitation recommendation, its key proofs for life after death, the description of the heavens, and its promise to "intercede for its reciter."', 'instructions' => '1. Read summary of Surah Al-Mulk.\n2. Key themes: Allah\'s dominion over all creation, creation of death and life as a test, descriptions of the heavens.\n3. Hadith: "It intercedes for its companion until he is forgiven."\n4. Goal: memorise the first 5 verses this week.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify Al-Mulk\'s themes and begin memorising the surah from its opening', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran and Science: Verses of the Universe', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Explore Quranic verses that describe the natural world (embryology, cosmology, water cycle, botany) and discuss the relationship between Quranic knowledge and modern science.', 'instructions' => '1. Read 5 Quranic verses on natural phenomena.\n2. Compare to modern scientific descriptions (not to prove — to appreciate).\n3. Discuss: why does the Quran encourage observation of nature? (As signs of Allah)\n4. Research one verse further and write a 1-paragraph reflection.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, reference materials', 'learning_objectives' => 'Connect 5 Quranic verses about the natural world to scientific observations', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Kahf: The Story of Musa and Khidr', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 35, 'difficulty' => 'hard', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Deep study of the Musa and Khidr story from Surah Al-Kahf — one of the most profound lessons in the Quran about divine wisdom, patience, and the limits of human knowledge.', 'instructions' => '1. Read the Musa and Khidr story (18:60–82) in full translation.\n2. Map the 3 events: the boat, the boy, the wall.\n3. For each: what seemed wrong? What was the hidden wisdom?\n4. Reflect: when has something in your life seemed bad but turned out to have a hidden blessing?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Analyse the 3 events in the Musa-Khidr story and apply their wisdom to real life', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Memorisation Tips: How to Memorise Quran Effectively', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn proven memorisation techniques for the Quran: repetition method, visual method, section-by-section, revision schedule, and the role of strong intention.', 'instructions' => '1. Discuss: what makes Quran memorisation different and special (it is ibadah, every letter is a reward).\n2. 5 techniques: read aloud repeatedly, chunk into 3-line sections, visualise the page, connect meaning to memory, revise before sleeping.\n3. Apply to one new verse using each technique.\n4. Design a personal revision schedule: new memorisation + daily revision.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Apply 5 memorisation techniques to a new verse and design a revision schedule', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran Etiquette: How to Treat the Holy Book', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 9, 'duration_minutes' => 20, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the adab (etiquette) of handling, reciting, and treating the Quran — from physical handling to spiritual preparation (wudu, intention, respect).', 'instructions' => '1. List 10 manners with the Quran: wudu before touching, placing it high, not putting anything on top, facing qiblah, not talking unnecessarily during recitation, stopping when yawning.\n2. Discuss: the Quran is the direct word of Allah — how does that change how we handle it?\n3. Role-play: demonstrate correct Quran etiquette from picking it up to placing it back.\n4. What would you teach a younger sibling about Quran manners?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran copy', 'learning_objectives' => 'Demonstrate 10 Quran etiquette rules in a role-play', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],


            // Quran 21-45
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Baqarah: The Longest Chapter', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'hard', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Overview the structure and major themes of Surah Al-Baqarah — guidance for believers, the story of Bani Israel, legal rulings, and the beautiful closing duas.', 'instructions' => '1. Overview: 286 verses, covers Bani Israel, rules on prayer, fasting, zakat, hajj, marriage, business.\n2. Map the major stories: Adam, Bani Israel, Ibrahim building Kaba, changing of Qiblah.\n3. Read the closing 2 verses (Amana-Rasul) — these are a special reward.\n4. Memorise the closing 2 verses and discuss their meaning.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify the major themes and stories of Surah Al-Baqarah and memorise its closing verses', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Reciting with Tarteel: Slow and Deliberate', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Understand and practise tarteel — reciting the Quran slowly and deliberately with full attention — as commanded in Surah Al-Muzzammil (73:4).', 'instructions' => '1. Read: "Recite the Quran with measured recitation." (73:4)\n2. Explain tarteel: each word is pronounced clearly with correct length and articulation.\n3. Recite 5 verses at normal speed then at tarteel pace.\n4. Compare: how does slower recitation help understanding?\n5. Practise tarteel on your favourite surah.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, recording device', 'learning_objectives' => 'Apply tarteel in recitation of a chosen surah and explain its spiritual benefits', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'The Story of Yusuf (AS): True Beauty of Character', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 8, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 35, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study the story of Yusuf (AS) from Surah Yusuf — the most beautiful story in the Quran — identifying its themes of patience, trust in Allah, and ultimate mercy.', 'instructions' => '1. Read a summary of Surah Yusuf (12).\n2. Timeline: dreams, jealousy, the well, Egypt, the prison, the king\'s dream, reunion.\n3. Lessons: sabr through trials, the consequences of jealousy, how Allah plans the best outcome.\n4. Write a 5-sentence reflection: what would you have done in Yusuf\'s position?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Narrate the story of Yusuf (AS) and extract 3 lessons applicable to personal life', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Rahman: Which Favours Will You Deny?', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Rahman — the surah of gratitude — listening to its rhythmic repetition and exploring the blessings of Allah it describes in creation and in Jannah.', 'instructions' => '1. Listen to a recitation of Al-Rahman (or recite together).\n2. Each time "Fa-bi-ayyi ala\'i rabbikuma tukadhdhibani" appears — pause: what blessing was just described?\n3. List 10 blessings from the surah.\n4. Reflect: what would you lose if you lost one of these blessings?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify 10 blessings described in Surah Al-Rahman and reflect on gratitude', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Waqf (Stopping Rules) in Recitation', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 8, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the waqf (stopping) symbols in the Quran — when to stop, when to continue, and when stopping is preferred — and practise applying them in recitation.', 'instructions' => '1. Introduce waqf symbols: mim (mandatory stop), la (do not stop), qif (stop), sad-la (permissible to stop), ra (preferable to continue).\n2. Identify each symbol in a selected passage.\n3. Recite the passage applying the waqf rules correctly.\n4. Discuss: why does the place of stopping matter for meaning?', 'materials_needed' => 'Tajweed Quran copy, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify and apply waqf (stopping) symbols correctly in a recitation passage', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'The Stories of the Prophets in the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Map all the major prophets mentioned in the Quran, identify which surahs tell their stories, and understand why Allah repeated their stories for the believers.', 'instructions' => '1. List 25 prophets mentioned in the Quran.\n2. For each: which surah contains their main story? What was their mission?\n3. Discuss: what themes recur in all prophetic stories (trial, rejection, patience, divine support)?\n4. Choose one prophet story to read in full this week.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, prophets reference list, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Map 25 Quranic prophets to their stories and identify recurring themes', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Waqiah: Reminder of the Day of Resurrection', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Waqiah (56) — its division of humanity into 3 groups, vivid descriptions of Jannah and Jahannam, and proofs of resurrection from nature.', 'instructions' => '1. Read Surah Al-Waqiah with translation.\n2. Identify the 3 groups: the foremost (As-Sabiqun), the right (As-habil-yamin), the left (As-habil-Shimal).\n3. Compare what is prepared for each.\n4. Proofs of resurrection: discuss the creation arguments in verses 57–74.\n5. Memorise the opening 5 verses.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify Al-Waqiah\'s 3 human groups, their outcomes, and memorise opening verses', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Makhaarij: Where Letters Come From', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the makhaarij al-huruf (articulation points of Arabic letters) — the 17 points in the mouth and throat from where each Arabic letter originates.', 'instructions' => '1. Introduce the 5 regions: throat (halq), tongue (lisaan), lips (shafatayn), nose (khayshum), upper palate (hanajara).\n2. Practise each throat letter: Hamza, Ha, Ain, Ghain, Kha, Ha.\n3. Practise each tongue group.\n4. Hear the difference between similar letters: Th/Dh, S/Sad, H/Ha.\n5. Record a recitation of Al-Fatiha, focusing on makhaarij.', 'materials_needed' => 'Tajweed guide, recording device', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify the 5 makhaarij regions and demonstrate correct articulation of at least 10 Arabic letters', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Keeping a Quran Reflection Journal', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Set up and begin a lifelong Quran reflection journal — recording ayahs that move you, what they mean, and how they relate to your daily life.', 'instructions' => '1. Set up journal: date, surah and verse number, the ayah in Arabic and translation, reflection (2–3 sentences).\n2. Begin with your favourite ayah.\n3. Continue for 14 days: one ayah per day.\n4. At the end: which ayah has the most entries? What does that tell you about what matters to you?', 'materials_needed' => 'Notebook, Quran, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Complete 14 journal entries each connecting an ayah to personal life reflection', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Understanding the Hijri Calendar in the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 8, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn what the Quran says about time (months, the sacred months, Ramadan) and understand the lunar calendar that governs Islamic worship.', 'instructions' => '1. Quran: "Indeed, the number of months with Allah is twelve months in the register of Allah." (9:36)\n2. Name all 12 Hijri months.\n3. Which 4 are sacred? What does sacred month mean?\n4. Why is Ramadan the most blessed month? What Quranic evidence is there?\n5. Convert today\'s date to Hijri.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, Hijri calendar, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Name all 12 Hijri months, identify the 4 sacred months, and explain the Quranic basis', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Imran: The Family of Imran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'hard', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Overview Surah Al-Imran — its stories of Maryam, Isa (AS), the mother of Maryam, and the battle of Uhud — with key lessons in trust, steadfastness, and prophetic mission.', 'instructions' => '1. Read introduction to Surah Al-Imran (3).\n2. Key stories: birth of Maryam, Zakariyya, birth of Isa (AS).\n3. Lessons from Uhud: why the Sahabah faced difficulty, the blessing of trials.\n4. Memorise the dua: "Rabbana la tuzigh quloobana ba\'da idh hadaytana..." (3:8)', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify Al-Imran\'s key stories and memorise one of its important duas', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Hijr: Preservation of the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study the Quranic promise of preservation: "Verily, it is We who sent down the reminder and it is We who will preserve it" (15:9) and how this is uniquely true for the Quran.', 'instructions' => '1. Read the verse and discuss: what does it mean to preserve a book for 1,400+ years?\n2. Discuss the evidence: millions of huffaz, unchanged text across all manuscripts.\n3. Compare to other major world texts and their variations.\n4. Reflect: what does it mean to you that the Quran you read is exactly what was revealed to the Prophet ﷺ?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, reference materials, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Explain the Quranic promise of preservation and cite evidence of its fulfilment', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Beautifying the Voice in Recitation', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Learn the hadith encouraging beautification of the voice when reciting the Quran and practise the techniques: melody within tajweed, pace, emotion, and presence.', 'instructions' => '1. Hadith: "Beautify the Quran with your voices." (Abu Dawud)\n2. Listen to 2 reciters with different styles (e.g., Sheikh Sudais, Sheikh Minshawi).\n3. What do you notice? What makes their recitation beautiful?\n4. Practise 5 verses: slow, with correct tajweed, and with genuine feeling.\n5. Record and share.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, recording device, audio examples', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify elements of beautiful Quranic recitation and apply them in a recorded practice', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran and Daily Dua: Verses That Are Prayers', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 11, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Collect 10 duas from the Quran — prayers of the prophets and believers — memorise them and incorporate them into daily life.', 'instructions' => '1. Collect 10 Quranic duas: Ibrahim\'s dua for the city (2:126), Musa\'s dua for help (28:24), Yunus in the whale (21:87), the closing dua of Al-Baqarah, etc.\n2. For each: memorise it, understand its meaning, and identify when to use it.\n3. Make a Dua card set and put them where you will see them.\n4. Use at least 3 in your du\'a this week.', 'materials_needed' => 'Index cards, Quran, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Memorise 10 Quranic duas and use at least 3 in personal prayer this week', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Review and Consolidation: My Quran Journey', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 7, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'A milestone review activity — recite surahs memorised, review tajweed rules learned, celebrate progress, and renew intention for the Quran journey ahead.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite all surahs memorised from memory (no Quran).\n2. Self-assess: tajweed rules you apply confidently vs. still working on.\n3. Review your Quran journal — best reflection from the series.\n4. Write a letter to yourself: where you started, how far you\'ve come, where you want to go.\n5. Make a fresh niyyah (intention) for the next phase.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, journal, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Complete a celebratory milestone review of Quran learning, renewing niyyah', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Hujurat: Community Ethics', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Hujurat (49) — the surah of social ethics — covering the prohibition of mockery, backbiting, suspicion, and the celebration of diversity.', 'instructions' => '1. Read Surah Al-Hujurat in full with translation.\n2. List every social prohibition mentioned.\n3. Discuss each: why is it harmful? What does it do to community?\n4. Apply to modern life: how do these rules apply to group chats and social media?\n5. Memorise one verse on Islamic brotherhood.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'List Al-Hujurat\'s social prohibitions and apply them to contemporary digital behaviour', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran and the Human Soul: Surah Al-Shams', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 8, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Shams (91) — the surah about the human soul and its purification — exploring the Quranic psychology of the nafs and how to nurture it toward goodness.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite and translate Surah Al-Shams.\n2. Focus: "He has succeeded who purifies it. He has failed who corrupts it." (91:9–10)\n3. Discuss: what purifies the soul? (prayer, dhikr, good deeds, tawbah)\n4. What corrupts it? (sin, heedlessness, bad companions)\n5. Write your personal soul-purification practice.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, notebook, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Explain the concept of nafs from Surah Al-Shams and identify personal soul-purification practices', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Halaqah: Group Quran Study Circle', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Run a family or sibling Quran halaqah: group recitation, one ayah taught by each member, questions, and collective dua — building the practice of community Quran learning.', 'instructions' => '1. Sit in a circle: each person recites one memorised surah or passage.\n2. Group selects one ayah to study: read, translate, discuss meaning.\n3. Each person: what does this ayah mean to YOU personally?\n4. One person leads a short dua related to the ayah studied.\n5. Set the date for the next halaqah.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, family/siblings', 'learning_objectives' => 'Lead and participate in a structured Quran halaqah, demonstrating community learning skills', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Understanding Naskh: Abrogation in the Quran', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 10, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'hard', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Introduction to the Quranic concept of naskh (abrogation) — where later verses modified or replaced earlier rulings — and why this was a mercy tailored to a developing community.', 'instructions' => '1. Explain: naskh is when a later revelation modified a previous ruling (e.g., the gradual prohibition of alcohol).\n2. Study one example: prohibition of alcohol — revealed in 3 stages.\n3. Why is this a mercy? The community needed gradual change.\n4. Discussion: naskh only applies to legal rulings, not theological truths. Why is this distinction important?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, reference materials, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Explain naskh with one clear example and describe why it was a mercy for the early Muslim community', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Surah Al-Fajr: Reflecting on Civilisations', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 9, 'age_max' => 12, 'duration_minutes' => 25, 'difficulty' => 'medium', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Study Surah Al-Fajr (89) — its reference to ancient civilisations (Aad, Thamud, Pharaoh) as warnings, and its beautiful ending describing the peaceful soul returning to Allah.', 'instructions' => '1. Recite and translate Surah Al-Fajr.\n2. Identify the 3 civilisations mentioned: what did they do and what was their end?\n3. The peaceful soul (nafs mutmainnah): "Return to your Lord, well-pleased and pleasing." Reflect on this.\n4. What does the surah teach about the purpose and end of material power?', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran, translation, notebook', 'learning_objectives' => 'Identify Al-Fajr\'s three civilisation warnings and reflect on its closing message about the peaceful soul', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],
            ['title' => 'Quran Memorisation Milestone: 5 Surahs', 'subject' => 'quran', 'age_min' => 6, 'age_max' => 9, 'duration_minutes' => 30, 'difficulty' => 'easy', 'is_free' => false, 'thumbnail_url' => null, 'description' => 'Celebrate the memorisation of a 5-surah milestone from Juz \'Amma — reciting all 5 from memory without any aid, receiving a certificate of achievement.', 'instructions' => '1. Student recites all 5 surahs from memory (no Quran).\n2. Parent or teacher marks: complete, minor errors, needs practice.\n3. Receive a written certificate (or drawn one!) for the accomplishment.\n4. Discuss: the Prophet ﷺ said every letter is a good deed — how many good deeds in 5 surahs?\n5. Set the next 5-surah target.', 'materials_needed' => 'Quran (for verification), certificate template, pencil', 'learning_objectives' => 'Recite 5 surahs from memory without assistance at milestone review', 'age_group' => 'school', 'is_muslim_only' => true],


